<HEADLINE> Wizards 2, Galaxy 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Alexi Lalas and Chris Klein scored  
first-half goals Saturday night, leading the Kansas City Wizards to 
a 2-1 win over the Los Angeles Galaxy. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first win of the season for Kansas City (1-7), which  
broke a Major League Soccer-record 10-game losing streak dating 
back to last season. Saturday's game was also the Wizards' first 
under former U.S. national team coach Bob Gansler, who replaced Ron 
Newman on April 29. 
</P>
<P>
	Kansas City's two goals doubled its total from the first seven  
games this season. 
