<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Blending Element Wins Yerba Buena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ALBANY, Calif. (AP) -- Blending Element overhauled pacesetter  
Queen Douna in the final strides to win the $200,000 Yerba Buena 
Handicap by a neck Saturday at Golden Gate Fields. 
</P>
<P>
	Receiving a heady ride from jockey Garrett Gomez, Blending  
Element tracked Queen Douna from the start. 
</P>
<P>
	Queen Douna, well rated on the lead by jockey Rafael Meza, dug  
in strongly down the stretch and just missed pulling off a 
front-running victory in the 1 3/8-mile turf race. 
</P>
<P>
	``She felt like she was just galloping (on the lead),'' Meza  
said. ``Garrett rode a smart race. He didn't try to burn me out and 
that's why we ran 1-2. When I went by the 3-16ths pole, I felt I 
was going to win because she really accelerated into the lane.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Blending Element, who won for the fourth time in her last five  
races, stopped the timer in 2:17.26. The 6-year-old mare provided 
trainer Carla Gaines with the biggest victory of her career and 
earned $120,000 for owner Warren B. Williamson. 
</P>
<P>
	Blending Element, at 8-5 the second choice in the betting behind  
3-2 favorite Midnight Line, paid $5.40, $3.60 and $2.40. Queen 
Douna went off at 13-1 and returned $7.80 and $3.20. Midnight Line, 
with Russell Baze up, paid $2.20 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Following the top three across the wire were Bates of Course,  
Raging Love and Squeak, a multiple stakes winner who finished last 
at 5-2. 
</P>
<P>
	Blending Element has eight victories, three seconds and a third  
in 18 career starts. The victory in the Yerba Buena boosted her 
earnings to $403,484. 
</P>
</TEXT>
