<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Missouri Student Dies in Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBIA, Mo. (AP) -- A student died early Saturday in a  
fraternity house fire at the University of Missouri-Columbia that 
was started by a burning candle, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Dominic L. Passantino, a freshman business major from Leawood,  
Kan., died in his room at the Sigma Chi house, said Assistant Fire 
Marshal Steve Sapp. 
</P>
<P>
	A preliminary autopsy showed that Passantino, whose age was not  
known, died of smoke inhalation. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said more than 40 other people who lived in the  
house also got out safely when the fire started about 5 a.m. during 
graduation weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire destroyed the room and damaged another room and a  
hallway on the third floor of the three-story house. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're celebrating graduation on one side of the campus, and  
here we've got this tragedy on the other side of the campus,'' said 
Charles Schroeder, assistant chancellor for student affairs at the 
university. 
</P>
</TEXT>
