<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Spielberg Plays Mr. Mom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Kate Capshaw's return to the movie set caused a  
role reversal at home. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was my summer to reign as king of the house, and I loved  
it,'' her husband, two-time Academy Award winner Steven Spielberg, 
says. 
</P>
<P>
	Spielberg, awarded an Oscar this year for his direction of  
``Saving Private Ryan,'' stayed home with the couple's seven 
children during Capshaw's seven-week shoot of ``The Love Letter,'' 
which opens May 21. Capshaw stars in the film and served as its 
producer. 
</P>
<P>
	After the movie wrapped, ``I was hardly ready to give her back  
the scepter,'' Spielberg says. ``There was a little power 
struggle.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Capshaw has given first priority to her family after marrying  
Spielberg in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've never been able to be on a set 14 hours a day and be the  
mother that I wanted to be,'' she tells US magazine in its June 
issue. In the couple's normal routine, she says, ``my little 
village is in the home, and his little village is the set.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
