<HEADLINE> Southern Cal. Honors Rosa Parks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Civil rights heroine Rosa Parks will receive  
an honorary doctorate from the University of Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am pleased you wish to honor me,'' the 86-year-old Parks  
told USC in a statement issued Friday. ``Each person must live 
their life as a model for others.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Parks' arrest in 1955 in Montgomery, Ala. for refusing to yield  
her bus seat to a white man set off a lengthy bus boycott led by 
Martin Luther King Jr. and provoked a Supreme Court challenge to 
the city's segregation law. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, President Clinton authorized Parks be awarded a  
Congressional Gold Medal, Congress' highest honor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
