<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapids 2, Burn 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- The Colorado Rapids won their fourth consecutive  
game Saturday night with a 2-1 shootout victory over the Dallas 
Burn. 
</P>
<P>
	In the tiebreaker, Colorado's Marquis White and Dallas' Leonel  
Alvarez each converted in the second round. In the fifth and final 
frame, Rapids reserve defender Chris Martinez scored on his shot, 
while Hahnemann saved Chad Deering's attempt to clinch the win. 
</P>
<P>
	Rapids goalkeeper Marcus Hahnemann had nine saves in regulation  
and three in the tiebreaker. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado midfielder Paul Bravo racked up his third goal of the  
season in the 80th minute by heading home Anders Limpar's corner 
kick. 
</P>
<P>
	With two minutes left, Burn forward Jason Kreis denied Colorado  
a regulation-time win with his league-leading seventh goal of the 
season. Following Hahnemann's point-blank save of Kreis' shot, 
Dante Washington tracked down the loose ball deep in the Rapids' 
box to again set up Kreis, whose goal forced the shootout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
