<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Solar Bound Streaks in Edgewood Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Solar Bound rallied from seventh on the  
backstretch, caught Tres Coronas outside the eighth pole and rolled 
to a six-length victory Saturday in the $114,800 Edgewood Stakes 
for 3-year-old fillies at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner, with Robby Albarado up, covered a mile on turf in  
1:36 2-5 and paid $5.80, $3.60 and $2.80. Secret Partner closed 
from last along the hedge to grab the place spot and paid $4.80 and 
$4. Suffragette finished another length back in third and paid 
$4.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Guy and Diane Snowden, Solar Bound won for the second  
time in as many starts this year and earned $71,176 to more than 
double her lifetime bankroll to $129,955. The victory was her third 
in four tries on the turf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
