<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lewinsky Satirizes Clinton on SNL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Monica Lewinsky poked fun and took a shot at  
President Clinton during a ``Saturday Night Live''appearance on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The former White House intern appeared in a skit as ex-President  
Clinton's Malibu housemate in 2001. Clinton, portrayed by actor 
Darell Hammond, is about to slip out for lunch with Vernon Jordan 
when Ms. Lewinsky arrives. 
</P>
<P>
	Hammond gives Ms. Lewinsky a slightly lewd embrace and asks  
about her day at work. 
</P>
<P>
	``Everyone gets so mad at me when I turn the wrong letters,''  
Ms. Lewinsky replied, a self-mocking reference to a job on ``The 
Wheel of Fortune.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hammond, dressed in a bathrobe, gives Lewinsky a gift: a copy of  
``Leaves of Grass.'' Ms. Lewinsky points out that he's already 
given her the book a couple of times. 
</P>
<P>
	Hammond tells Ms. Lewinsky that he has to get going, and she is  
suspicious. 
</P>
<P>
	``Don't you trust me?'' he asks.  
</P>
<P>
	``In your dreams, you big creep,'' Ms. Lewinsky replies,  
followed by the traditional show-opener: ``Live from New York, it's 
Saturday night!'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lewinsky referred to Clinton as ``the big creep'' while  
Linda Tripp secretly recorded her. 
</P>
<P>
	Even though word had slipped out that Ms. Lewinsky had attended  
rehearsals this week, NBC refused to say whether she would be on 
the show. Actor Cuba Gooding Jr. was host and Ricky Martin was 
musical guest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
