<HEADLINE> Revolution 1, Fusion 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Substitute Paulo Dos Santos provided all  
the footwork New England needed Saturday night as the Revolution 
gained its first home win of the season, a 1-0 shootout victory 
over Miami. 
</P>
<P>
	Dos Santos scored the winning goal in the shootout, the fourth  
of the year for each team. 
</P>
<P>
	Except for the final minutes of regulation, scoring  
opportunities were few and far between in the sloppily played match 
before 11,173 at rain-soaked Foxboro Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	Kris Kelderman, Tony Kuhn and Dos Santos scored in the ensuing  
shootout for New England (3-4) while Henry Gutierrez and Jim Rooney 
scored for last-placed Miami (3-5). 
</P>
<P>
	Each team came close to putting the game away in the final  
minutes of regulation. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami's Nelson Vargas had two shots blocked by goalkeeper Jeff  
Causey, from 14 yards at 80 minutes and from 12 yards in the 89th. 
</P>
<P>
	New England's Edwin Gorter blasted a 30-yard shot off the left  
post at 85 minutes. 
