<HEADLINE> Johnson Sprints to Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT-DE-FRANCE, Martinique (AP) -- Olympic champion Michael  
Johnson electrified Fort-de-France stadium Saturday afternoon by 
winning the men's 200-meter dash during an IAAF meet on this French 
Caribbean island. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson majestically won the race in 20.07 seconds and was feted  
with a standing ovation from the thousands in the grandstands. 
</P>
<P>
	Lindford Christie, the Olympic 100-meter champion in 1992, was  
injured and couldn't compete but received an ovation when he walked 
onto the track to greet the crowd. 
</P>
<P>
	Americans dominated the 100-meter dash as well, with Milton  
Mallard winning in 10.33. 
</P>
<P>
	Jamaica ran 1-2 in the men's 400-meter hurdles, with Kemel  
Thompson winning in 49.19 and Jan Weakley claiming second in 49.76. 
</P>
<P>
	In the women's 100, Endurance Ojokolo of Nigeria beat defending  
meet champion Petya Pendareva by .02 seconds in 11.39. 
</P>
</TEXT>
